\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
James drew on his cigarette and threw his head back, letting off a small
 cloud of smoke.
 He was smiling when he pointed to Ethan and said:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Not much to hide, Ethan.
 Sometimes I smoke.
 Usually alone.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan nodded with a sly grin on his face.
 He sipped another mouthful from his glass of scotch which was disappearing
