 nurse with the outspoken dislike of journalists and other vermin that seemed
 to feed on human misery: As she sat there smoking, she struck Ethan as
 a very familiar face, someone close but yet so distant in memory.
 Like a long lost friend or perhaps, a lover.
 He kept trying to remember, and was soon enthralled by the warmth of her
 face, lost in his little own box of memories.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
