\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Just doing my job, major, sir,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 replied Ethan with a faint smile, his eyes still trying to steal a glimpse
 of Nicole; she must've really gone, he thought to himself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sisters were huddled close together, as if waiting for a verdict on
 them.
 The sister superior was eyeing him and the leader of the bandits intensely.
 Maybe she was thinking of doing something stupid herself.
 That would complicate things right when he was trying to achieve a sense
 of rapprochement, if anything like that could be achieved with the likes
 of these people.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I'm no major, Dick.
 I'll call you Dick.
 No Major Yuembe anymore.
 I'm King, King Yuembe!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 shouted the so-called Major, triumphantly raising both arms in the air.
 He fired off a couple of shots, eliciting a response of wild shots in the
 air from his men who cheered and eyed the sisters with venomous stares.
 They looked barely able to hold themselves; another example in forced disciplin
e.
 He laughed heartily once more, before settling down his gaze towards Ethan
 once more.
 Ethan pitched the idea of the story he had been working on in his mind:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I think you'd make the perfect story, really.
 I could show the world your living conditions, the way you're defending
