 He grabbed the sister superior by one arm, while she was clearly paying
 no attention to her surroundings, her face deathly pale, her eyes without
 focus.
 Instinctively she tried to shake him off.
 He caught her stare and tried to convey a sense of calm.
 Panic wouldn't get them anywhere; it could only lead to senseless death.
 He told her then while stray shots seemed to edge dangerously close judging
 by the plaster and chipped wood flying around them:
