\begin_layout Standard
James was overlooking a large map of the area west of the Niger, stretched
 out against a wall of his shadowy office.
 Small pins marked places of interest, unit positions and enemy contacts.
 His hand traced a road to the east, and then he placed another, different
 sort of marker pin there, before smiling thinly to himself.
 He paced around the office with hands behind his back, and stopped for
 a while to take a look outside; he opened the window blinds and gleaming
 white sunlight filled the room.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
