\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he said, and yawned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

You'll fall asleep on the wheel if you go on like this.
 You need to get some rest,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 she said, looking worried.
 Ethan glanced at her sideways and kept driving, seemingly about to pass
 out in any moment.
 He shook his head drowsily without replying.
 Nicole insisted:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Look, if you won't let me drive at least pull over and get some sleep.
 For God's sake.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan drew a deep breath and shook himself trying to stay alert.
 He told her then without taking his eyes off the road, his voice shallow,
 almost resigned:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

