 on his face when without warning Ethan reached for his ankle and pulled
 his combat knife with one superbly fluid motion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nicole's eyes widened with shock while Adu's hands were already upending
 the table.
 She only had time enough to cry 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Wait!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 but Ethan was already off his chair, trying to sidestep the table.
 He went for Adu's arm with a quick jab with the knife, but he missed for
 an inch or so.
 The upturned table hadn't slowed him down, and he was right behind Adu
 who was already thrusting people aside, edging his way towards the bar.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sudden commotion made people turn their heads in a snap.
 Nicole jumped off her chair and tried to grab Ethan by the waist.
 Her initial surprise had made her slow to act and she missed him by a few
 inches, grasping nothing but air.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Within moments, Adu had cleared his way through the tables, smashing glasses
 and brushing aside stunned customers.
 Ethan was only a few steps behind, his knife in hand.
 A quick nod and a moment later, the bartender was leaning behind the counter.
 When saw the movement he instinctively rushed towards the ground in an
 audacious tackle.
 Their feet connected; Adu tripped and suddenly fell sideways at the exact
 moment when a small cloud of wooden splinters, smashed tiles and pieces
 of cloth flew right above Ethan's head.
 The booming sound of a shotgun echoed like thunderclap around the small
 bar; mayhem ensued.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Shouts and cries mingled with the sudden rush of screeching tables and chairs
 as the panicked customers fled the 'Madimba'.
 Clicking metallic sounds alerted Ethan that the shotgun was being reloaded,
 even as Adu had rolled on his back and turned around to jump on Ethan.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With his sudden rush he had managed to pin Ethan's knife hand, but his grip
 was lax, his body badly placed, vulnerable.
 Ethan managed to swing a punch right in Adu's face with his free hand;
 it barely shook him.
 A couple more quick jabs had little effect other than Adu replying with
 a fist right in Ethan's stomach, grunting instinctively as he flexed his
 muscles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan tried to get a hold on Adu with his legs, catch him in a vice.
 He couldn't get a good grip, as Adu was piled up more pressure on his knife
 hand, trying to wrestle the knife away.
 His other hand went for Ethan's neck and met with opposition.
 While they grappled on the floor, Ethan heard a loud shot without warning,
 then another and one more, all in quick succession.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The crowd rushing outside reacted to the shots with a louder burst of bewildered
, panicked shouts.
 They were still shouting when he heard the thud of a body falling limp
 against the floor, the sound of smashed glass following its way down.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They were both surprised and for an instant Adu's attention waned as he
 shot a reflexive look behind him, where the bartender should have been
 holding the shotgun.
 In that single moment his grip became just a tad more lax and allowed Ethan
 to slip his knife hand away with a sudden, violent shove.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Losing the grip on the knife hand, Adu tried to roll over on the floor,
 put some space between them.
 He tried to put his back against the bar, while he reached for someplace
 out of Ethan's sight.
 While he swung his body around, trying to catch Adu from an ankle or a
 leg, he saw Adu's face suddenly go slack, all the tension vanishing in
 an instant.
 His hand stayed for the merest moment still in the air, and then another
 shot was heard.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This time he saw Adu's whole body flex, quiver and shudder all in the blink
 of an eye before it fell limp against the bottom of the bar.
 Blood trailed down from the hole in his shaven head, now grossly disfigured,
 the cracked skull penetrating the skin.
 Nicole's shouts reawakened Ethan who stood there transfixed for the merest
 second, mesmerized from the puzzled look in Adu's eyes:
