\begin_layout Standard
The inside of the mansion was decorated in classic early-colonial French
 style, naturally including an oversized chandelier.
 Intricate, expensive looking vases and crystal glassware showcases could
 be seen on either side of a large hallway.
 Louis XV furniture and large portraits of family members filled in the
 living room; every corner was designed to instill a sense of luxury, and
 money.
 Even the floors were made of high-quality spotless wooden planks, polished
 and flaring even in the evening light.
