 and began a slow, careful descend right in the middle of the clearing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan could see James through the cockpit, smiling thinly.
 As the helicopter began touching down, both him and Andy crouched low and
 tried to shield their faces from the updraft created from the rotor blades
 that sent sand and mud flying towards them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The helicopter touched down with closed side-doors.
 Ethan noticed the engine pitch was going down as well; the rotor blades
 were spinning down.
 James had powered the helicopter down for some reason.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Andy was looking at James warily, while Ethan shook his head to reassure
 him.
 He himself though, was feeling something was amiss.
 James opened the cockpit door and jumped off the helicopter.
 He was wearing the standard issue flight suit, complete with helmet which
 he promptly removed, and let the rain wash over his face.
 He blinked and tasted the rain for a moment, before he smiled at Ethan.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan smiled back somewhat awkwardly and told him:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

