\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Because you're not leaving,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 James said and pointed the gun at Andy who had precious little time to
 remember that he had heard James' voice somewhere before.
 And then Andy was already lying on his back; the power of the shot had
 sent him flying a couple of feet, his shoulder a torn mess.
 His vision became blurry from the pain, the wound feeling hot like molten
 iron.
 Ethan instead of rushing towards James had remained stunned, unable to
 comprehend what had just happened.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Jesus, you shot Andy.
 Why the fuck did you just shoot Andy?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 cried Ethan, as he tried to tend to his brother, rolling around the muddied
 ground, bleeding, and in pain.
 Ethan took out what few things remained from the medical kit, to at least
 stop the bleeding.
 James replied then with a deep, sombre voice:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Because I want you to feel the pain, Ethan,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he said and took another clear shot at Andy.
 Andy's body stopped moving as it jerked once and then became limp.
 Ethan saw Andy with a frowned stare and an entry wound in his forehead.
 Pieces of skull and brain matter were lying on the mud near his slightly
 deformed head.
 His brother, was dead.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He felt he was going to go mad at that instant, blood rising up in his head
 which was about to explode; James voice made him turn around and face him
 with the simple intent of killing him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Look at your dead brother, Ethan.
 God smiled upon you today, Ethan.
 Because you had time to see him one last time.
 I never did,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he said, shaking his head slowly, cooly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan cried out in anguish and slumped himself besides his brother's body,
 unable to even stand upright.
 The upheaval of feeling was tremendous.
 Ethan felt everything all at once: infuriated and cheated, guilty and beaten
 down, ready to kill and simply waiting to die.
 He merely found the strength to ask with a crippled voice:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Why? Whatever for?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

For Enkele, my brother.
 My flesh and blood.
 My only hope in this world,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 said James through grating teeth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I don't..
 I don't understand,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 said Ethan with a terribly confused voice, his face utterly broken.
 James swallowed hard and wiped some of the rain off his forehead.
 He almost shouted rather than talked:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Kenya! It was you.
 The freedom fighters.
 It was your long range patrol, Ethan! It wasn't about the lives of your
 men, though.
 You had a choice, and you still pulled the trigger.
 You killed my brother in cold blood.
 It was you!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he cried, the gun not waving an inch from his hand, aimed straight at Ethan's
 chest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ethan stammered, barely able to find the words: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I didn't..
 I didn't know.
 It was war, James, for God's sake! How could I've known!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he yelled indignantly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

But I did.
 I learned.
 Normally I could never have hoped to find out, but fate chose otherwise.
 And then I had no choice: I had to kill your brother.
 An eye for an eye, Ethan!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 he cried with misplaced fervor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

You mean, you knew? What did you know?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 asked Ethan with a deep frown and a hint of fear in his voice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Everything!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 cried James and laughed bitterly, tears running down his maddened eyes
 before he continued:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I was their source inside Lagos, Ethan! And I knew things about them.
 What I didn't know, I learned in the process.
 And so it came that I knew your brother wasn't really missing.
 And then I wanted you to go after him, find him for me.
 Do all the dirty work.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Revenge? This was all about fucking revenge?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 asked James with an angry cry.
 James replied calmly, with a seemingly ever-widening grin attached to his
 face.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

No.
 You're right, you're a smart man.
 It couldn't be just about a feeling now, could it? A simple, pure feeling?
 There was more, I'll admit.
 I saw the flames on the way here.
 A job well done.
 With Andy and Nicole dead, the French organization's almost wiped out.
 The Biafrans will not hold out for long.
 Playing both will make me a rich, black man in a poor, african country.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Money and revenge? Is that fair game for the death of your brother? Of my
 brother?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 asked Andy with real anger and fearful stressing his voice further.
